  "summary": "Malicious code in metavu (npm)",
  "details": "The preinstall hook (node index.js) collects host system information — hostname, platform, architecture, home directory, username/uid/gid/shell, OS type/release, total/free memory, CPU count, whoami, id, and current working directory — and POSTs it as a JSON payload to hxxps://4f54203c-996c-4f52-b136-ef9b1fd0f64d/detox56. The package also ships a file containing scraped Instagram account data. The version number is set to an artificially high value (99.21.1-1.21.127) to appear as a newer version in automated installers.",
